Jenna Etheridge, News24An inside view of the car crash. (Michael Hauser) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; Staff at an estate agency in Gardens, Cape Town, had a lucky escape when a car crashed through their storefront on Friday.&ldquo;I was in the office and suddenly heard tyres screeching. The next thing our window breaks and we had staff running away and screaming,&rdquo; agent Michael Hauser told News24.&ldquo;Thank goodness nobody was sitting at the desk in that corner. It is the angels&rsquo; protection.&rdquo;The employee was apparently having coffee elsewhere.Hauser said he got quite a shock. He sent out a notification and paramedics were on the scene within minutes.Traffic along Kloof Street came to a halt following the crash.A minibus taxi reportedly rear-ended a Honda Jazz on the corner of Kloof and Upper Union streets, causing the latter to ram into the office, Wheels24 reported. Bystander Jenna Bruwer said: "Apparently the taxi's brakes failed and he rear-ended the Honda Jazz."&nbsp;Nobody was injured and the accident was being investigated, Western Cape Emergency Services said.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.